# Framework philosophy (must follow)

When editing or adding code in this project, follow **[PHILOSOPHY.md](PHILOSOPHY.md)**. Summary:

- **No custom event loop in macros.** Build StChain, Init, Make loop, Finish; the framework controls the loop.
- **Physics in StMaker subclasses.** Implement Init(), Make(), Clear(), Finish(); histograms in DeclareHistograms() / WriteHistograms().
- **Makers are compiled.** Code in `StMaker/StXXXMaker/`, built to `lib/libStXXXMaker.so`.
- **Macros under root4star.** Entry is a ROOT macro; `script/run_anaXxx.sh` sets env and calls it.
- **YAML-driven config.** Cuts and histograms from YAML via ConfigManager; change without recompiling.
- **No hardcoding.** Put all cut values, thresholds, and analysis parameters in YAML config.
- **One config per concern.** One maker config per StMaker; one cut config per cut type (event, track, pid, v0, mixing). Mainconf references each.
- **Mainconf as single entry point.** `config/mainconf/main_<anaName>.yaml` references all other configs; scripts take mainconf as primary argument.

For full wording and "Why two macros", see [PHILOSOPHY.md](PHILOSOPHY.md). In case of conflict, **PHILOSOPHY.md** is the source of truth.
